Koler

This ransomware family first appeared in May 2014 and it blocks the screen of an infected device and requests a ransom between $100 and $300 in order to unlock the device. This request is sent through a localized message from the "police".

However, ransomwares belonging to this family do not encrypt any files or perform any kind of advanced blocking of the target device other than blocking the screen.
